  "final": {
    "response": 12,
    "explanation": "No convincing evidence that Reader View improves reading speed for participants with dyslexia. In the dyslexia subgroup, Welch t-test on log(speed) was not significant (p=0.908, d=0.011), Mann-Whitney was not significant (p=0.732), and adjusted OLS within dyslexia showed a near-zero Reader View effect (coef=0.0219, p=0.684). The ReaderView*dyslexia interaction in full-sample OLS was also not significant (p=0.685). Custom interpretable models (SmartAdditiveRegressor and HingeEBMRegressor), fit on both full and dyslexia-only data, did not surface Reader View as a dominant positive driver relative to other covariates."
  }
